 "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Extract JPEG thumbnail.\n\n(Thankfully the JPEG data is stored as a unit.)"]}, {"name": "exifread.classes.ExifHeader.decode_maker_note", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Decode all the camera-specific MakerNote formats\n\nNote is the data that comprises this MakerNote.\nThe MakerNote will likely have pointers in it that point to other\nparts of the file. We'll use self.offset as the starting point for\nmost of those pointers, since they are relative to the beginning\nof the file.\nIf the MakerNote is in a newer format, it may use relative addressing\nwithin the MakerNote. In that case we'll use relative addresses for\nthe pointers.\nAs an aside: it's not just to be annoying that the manufacturers use\nrelative offsets.  It's so that if the makernote has to be moved by the\npicture software all of the offsets don't have to be adjusted.  Overall,\nthis is probably the right strategy for makernotes, though the spec is\nambiguous.\nThe spec does not appear to imagine that makernotes would\nfollow EXIF format internally.  Once they did, it's ambiguous whether\nthe offsets should be from the header at the start of all the EXIF info,\nor from the header at the start of the makernote.\n\nTODO: look into splitting this up"]}, {"name": "exifread.classes.ExifHeader._canon_decode_tag", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mn_tags", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Decode Canon MakerNote tag based on offset within tag.\n\nSee http://www.burren.cx/david/canon.html by David Burren", "TODO Decode Olympus MakerNote tag based on offset within tag.", "def _olympus_decode_tag(self, value, mn_tags):", "pass"]}, {"name": "exifread.classes.ExifHeader._canon_decode_camera_info", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "camera_info_tag", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Decode the variable length encoded camera info section."]}, {"name": "exifread.classes.ExifHeader.parse_xmp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "xmp_bytes", "type": {"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Adobe's Extensible Metadata Platform, just dump the pretty XML."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Handle an EXIF header."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "exifread.tags.makernote.nikon", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "exifread.tags.makernote.nikon.ev_bias", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "seq", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["First digit seems to be in steps of 1/6 EV.\nDoes the third value mean the step size?  It is usually 6,\nbut it is 12 for the ExposureDifference.\nCheck for an error condition that could cause a crash.\nThis only happens if something has gone really wrong in\nreading the Nikon MakerNote.\nhttp://tomtia.plala.jp/DigitalCamera/MakerNote/index.asp"]}], "variables": [{"name": "exifread.tags.makernote.nikon.TAGS_NEW", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "exifread.tags.makernote.nikon.TAGS_OLD", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "exifread.tags.makernote.canon", "documentation": ["Makernote (proprietary) tag definitions for Canon.\n\nhttp://www.sno.phy.queensu.ca/~phil/exiftool/TagNames/Cano